-When would you want to create a remote repository rather than keeping your work in local?
I should create a remote repository when I have to collaborate with someone or I want to ask for help to online users.


-Why might you want to always pull changes manually rather than having Git automatically stay up-to-date with your remote repository?
Because sometimes you may want to test something before publish it or you want to create a branch that won't be accessible to the others.

-Describe the differences between forks, clones, and branches. When would you use one instead of another?
branch crea all'interno della repository un "braccio" che partendo dall'originale sviluppa funzioni differenti e che in caso viene ricollegato tramite merge al file principale. Clone crea una copia della repository tale e quale da remoto a locale con annesse commits.
Fork crea una copia virtuale della repository che successivamente potrà essere copiata in locale. la copia non andrà a intaccare l'originale.